  "prompt": "What are the best activities to do with children when visiting Timisoara, Romania?",
  "response": "Timisoara offers several kid-friendly activities:\n\n1. Parks and Outdoor Spaces\n- Roses Park (Parcul Rozelor)\n- Children's Park (Parcul Copiilor)\n- Central Park (Parcul Central)\n\n2. Museums\n- Banat Village Museum (open-air museum with traditional houses)\n- Natural History Museum\n- Interactive Science Center Lists (great for children)\n\n3. Attractions\n- Zoo Timisoara\n- Theresia Bastion (historic fortress)\n- Timi\u0219oara Water Park (summer activity)\n\n4. Entertainment\n- Puppet Theater (Teatrul de P\u0103pu\u0219i Merlin)\n- Iulius Town Mall (play areas and entertainment)\n- Cinema City for family movie screenings\n\n5. Cultural Activities\n- Liberty Square (historical center with fountains)\n- Orthodox Cathedral\n- Metropolitan Cathedral\n\n6. Recreational Activities\n- Bicycle rides along the Bega River\n- Boat rides during summer\n- Picnics in local parks\n\n7. Seasonal Events\n- Festival of Flowers\n- Christmas Market\n- Various children's festivals throughout the year\n\nThese activities offer a mix of educational, cultural, and fun experiences for children visiting Timisoara.",
